summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackBrows so lifted - it's CRAZY! The Brow Glue Crazy Lift. Up to 16HR strong hold clear brow lamination gel with a built-in styling comb to lift each hair.
details: DetailsFeaturesLamination gel with up to 24H hold. Universal clear, transparent formulaBuilt in styling comb that evenly dispenses glue & grips onto every hair for maximum lift. Instantly lifts and laminates brows!Flake proof. reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Minimal packaging, although the outer carton was obscenely large for the tube. The applicator makes it easy to apply and the product smells as an eye product does.  The price point is perfect for the size and amount of product.

reviews.headline: Works great but don't use too much!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This works great and is super strong and long lasting, but I will warn you not to use too much because it can pull and you can see the product residue on your brows.

reviews.headline: Works well
reviews.comments: It's a solid brow gel that does the job. I think it's hard for a clear brow gel to be revolutionary, but this one works well and keeps my brows in place for the entire day. It feels fine and does not tend to flake off if I touch my face during the day.

reviews.headline: great hold but flakes after a while
reviews.comments: this product has a great hold to it and lifted up my eyebrows but the flakes get horrible after a couple hours and then it just looks messy

-kept my brows in place for a long time even while i taught dance lessons
-initially hard to squeeze out but once it started coming out, it was smooth sailing

reviews.headline: BEST brow gel out!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] NYX Cosmetics Crazy Glue Brow Lift gives a strong, laminated look without the salon visit. The clear gel sets quickly and really locks brows into place, holding all day without flaking. The applicator makes it easy to brush brows up or shape them precisely. Works especially well for thinner or unruly brows, but if your brows are very thick, you may need to layer for extra hold. A budget-friendly option for that lifted, sculpted brow trend.

reviews.headline: Must have
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] No smell great application cute packaging great bang for your buck. Very well made product easy to use last all day a must have beauty product!!!

reviews.headline: I will definitely buy this again and again
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Oh, this is a cute little glue the packaging design and everything is perfect. I'm gonna have to try the application and see how precise it is, but the glue is kind of strong.

reviews.comments: Its so flacky, Doesn't hold, and werid application. I bought it because i coudnt find the brow glue but now im going to have to return it. I also dislile that i cant see how much product i have left

reviews.headline: Don't Buy
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product is not effective. With every use, an immense amount of product remains in the applicator which makes it messy. It also mixes the product with your foundation, and doesn't have lasting power. Pro is that it's cheap

reviews.headline: Great hold BUT flakes like crazy
reviews.comments: Love the applicator and how great the hold is when first applied. However, like many of the other reviews have stated the flakes after just a few hours are insane. I'm going to stick with the NYX Brow Glue that has great hold and doesnt flake at all. If they can get the same formula of the "Brow Glue" into this "Crazy Lift" version I would definitely be open to trying it again.

reviews.headline: Best brow glue by far
reviews.comments:
Brow glues I have used in the past do not live up to this one by Nyx. I have the type of eyebrows that grow downwards and other products don't have the type of good hold to keep them in place. This one by Nyx is the BEST one yet and it's better than even their own line of brow glue products. This glue keeps everything in place during my shift gives that laminated look. 

Yes it does flake but it can be solved by simply smoothing it over gently with your finger! Best glue ever!

reviews.headline: Good Brow Glue!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This brow glue does the job. It's easy to apply with the bristle applicator. There's no harsh scent and it lasts all day. A little goes a long way so one tube will definitely last a while.

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The NYT Brow Crazy Glue is an absolute game-changer! I've tried so many brow gels, but nothing holds my brows in place like this one. The hold is strong enough to keep them perfectly lifted and shaped all day, yet it doesn't feel crunchy or heavy. It gives that sleek, laminated look without the hassle of an actual lamination treatment.

The brush is the perfect size for precise application, and a little product goes a long way, so it lasts for months. I love that it dries clear and doesn't flakeâ€”my brows look polished from morning to night, even through workouts and humid weather.

If you're serious about keeping your brows looking flawless and on-point all day, NYT Brow Crazy Glue is worth every penny. It's my new holy grail!

reviews.headline: Bad Product
reviews.comments: I have tried the NYX original glue and it sucked. I was excited to try this product but it was as disappointing. The product is advertised as long lasting but its false. The brow lift does not last. It has been an hour since I applied the product and the brow lift is gone. This product will just leave your eyebrows looking crusty because this product has a very flaky result. I would definitely recommend spending a few more dollars instead to buy a higher end brow gel that won't cause your eyebrow hairs to fall off and leave your skin looking crusty.
VERY FLAKY does not provide a crazy lift as advertised. Just as bad as the original glue.

reviews.headline: Good product
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The NYX brow soap has strong hold â€” my brows stayed in place all day, which I really liked.
However, it leaves a white residue on the brow hairs after it dries, making them look messy and not clean. The hold is great, but the finish ruins the overall look. Unfortunately, I wouldn't repurchase.

reviews.headline: Good product
reviews.comments: Brow Glue is a professional gel that delivers a lamination effect at home, does not dry out or leave stickiness, and holds the brow shape all day. It's safe for those who value skincare benefits.

reviews.headline: Love the lift, hate the flakes!
reviews.comments: Loveeeeee how this looks when you first apply it! Love the lamination and lift it gives i just HATE how flakey and crusty it looks afterwards, not cute at all. Really really like the silicone-like brush tip I feel like it does a good job at getting all the hairs laid.

reviews.headline: They definitely stuck
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review Honestly wasn't expecting this to work as well as it does. My brows stayed up like they had a military contract. No flaking, no crust, and zero weird smell. It dries quick (but not panic-fast), and gives that laminated look without the salon price tag. I've tried more expensive gels that didn't hold half as well. A little goes a long way, so the value's solid. Bonusâ€”it didn't fight my makeup or give me that dried glue look. Definitely a staple in the chaos drawer.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I honestly didn't expect to fall this hard for an eyebrow product, but NYX's The Brow Glue is a game-changer. I've tried high-end brow gels, soap brows, waxesâ€”you name itâ€”and none of them have held up (literally) like this one does.

ðŸ§´ The Application:
The packaging is small but mighty. The brush is tiny and precise, which I loveâ€”it lets me coat every little brow hair without making a mess. The formula comes out clear and feels slightly tacky at first, but don't let that scare you. Once it sets (which takes less than a minute), your brows are locked in all day. No flaking, no stiffness, no weird residue.

ðŸ’ª The Hold:
I have thick, slightly unruly brows, and this is the only product that keeps them laminated-looking from morning until night. Whether I'm going for a brushed-up editorial vibe or just need to tame strays, it gets the job done without overdoing it. You can even use it before brow pencil or powder to get that feathery shape and then fill inâ€”it doesn't smudge your other products.

ðŸ’° The Price:
It's under $10?! For something that performs this well? Total steal. I've actually ditched my $25+ brow waxes for this. NYX really understood the assignment here.

ðŸ”„ Bonus Tip:
If you want the ultimate laminated effect, brush the glue through your brows, press them down gently with the handle of the spoolie, and let it set. It gives that clean, sculpted editorial finish you see all over TikTok.
The scent is pretty unrecognizable which I love about a product and the packaging really makes it stand out! 

â¸»

Final Verdict:

If you want brows that don't budge, a formula that doesn't flake or crunch, and a price that doesn't make you cryâ€”NYX The Brow Glue is 100% worth it. I've already bought backups. This is one of those products that once you try, you don't go back.
faceoff_positive.headline: Little tube of magic!

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. So this is an interesting product. I like that this brow glue is invisible, not brown or red. I like that it doesn't leave big chunky residue. I like that it comes in the adorable super glue style packaging.  But- I  didn't like the brush, or how hard it is to get the correct amount squeezed out, it always feels like it's too little or too much. I've tried to warm the tube up in my hands a bit by squishing it around with the lid on. It was still very hard to squeeze out. The brush is... meh. It seems to work ok at styling the finished look but not so much at brushing the brows backwards. Something isn't working correctly,  either there's not enough tackiness or the comb  is just too short or the shape is weird. Overall,  it's not bad,  and holds decently but does flake a tiny little bit. I would say I'd recommend if you don't mind that there's a learning curve. It's an inexpensive brow gel and it being clear is definitely a bonus! It does hold really well.
faceoff_negative.headline: A decent gel but a learning curve
